Testing #286024

In the settings define:
```
{
    "chat.tools.terminal.autoApprove": {
        "/^whoami --help$/": {
            "approve": false,
            "matchCommandLine": true
        },
    }
}
```
In chat ask: `what command line arguments does whoami support?`

Note the funny way of rendering the reply

<img width="598" height="343" alt="Image" src="https://github.com/user-attachments/assets/b45a3107-1f68-40fc-a131-16d9f16638fb" />

Testing #286005

* have the keybindings config below
* open terminal suggestions
* :bug: the label and help text still talks about `Tab`


```
// Place your key bindings in this file to override the defaults
[
    {
        "key": "cmd+p",
        "command": "workbench.action.terminal.acceptSelectedSuggestion",
        "when": "simpleSuggestWidgetHasFocusedSuggestion && terminalFocus && terminalHasBeenCreated && terminalIsOpen && terminalSuggestWidgetVisible || simpleSuggestWidgetHasFocusedSuggestion && terminalFocus && terminalIsOpen && terminalProcessSupported && terminalSuggestWidgetVisible"
    },
    {
        "key": "tab",
        "command": "-workbench.action.terminal.acceptSelectedSuggestion",
        "when": "simpleSuggestWidgetHasFocusedSuggestion && terminalFocus && terminalHasBeenCreated && terminalIsOpen && terminalSuggestWidgetVisible || simpleSuggestWidgetHasFocusedSuggestion && terminalFocus && terminalIsOpen && terminalProcessSupported && terminalSuggestWidgetVisible"
    }
]
```

